# Backend Standards

Each module contains:
router.py       ← API endpoints only
service.py      ← Business logic only
repository.py   ← Database access only
schemas.py      ← Pydantic v2 request/response models
models.py       ← ORM models
dependencies.py ← FastAPI dependency injection
constants.py    ← Module constants
exceptions.py   ← Module exception classes

Layer rules (strictly enforced):
- router.py calls service.py only — never repository.py
- service.py calls repository.py only — never raw DB sessions
- repository.py owns all SQL and ORM queries
- Never place business logic in router.py

Python standards:
- Type hints required on every function (args + return type)
- mypy --strict must pass with zero errors
- Pydantic v2 for all schemas
- Dependency injection via FastAPI Depends()

Never use print() — use structlog structured logging.

Imports:
- Absolute imports only
- from app.modules.<module>.<file> import <Name>
